billion primarily due to the impact of COVID-19, inclusive of the suspension of production and austerity measures as well as cost
savings associated with transformation activities and savings related to the wind-down of Holden sales, design and engineering
operations and sale of our vehicle and powertrain manufacturing facilities in Thailand; and (3) decreased costs of $0.3 billion
related to parts and accessories sales; partially offset by (4) a benefit of $1.4 billion related to the retrospective recoveries of
indirect taxes in Brazil in 2019; (5) increased material and freight costs of $0.9 billion; (6) charges of $0.7 billion
