Adjusted Automotive Free Cash Flow We measure adjusted automotive free cash flow as automotive operating cash flow from
continuing operations less capital expenditures adjusted for management actions. For the year ended December 31, 2020, net
automotive cash provided by operating activities under U.S. GAAP was $7.5 billion, capital expenditures were $5.3 billion and
adjustments for management actions, primarily related to GMI restructuring, were $0.3 billion. For the year ended December 31,
2019, net automotive cash provided by operating activities under U.S. GAAP was $7.4 billion, capital expenditures were $7.5
billion and adjustments for management actions, primarily related to transformation activities, were $1.2 billion.
